race.description: For The Love Of Frieda Maiden Plate
race.comment: CONTALDO (1) overcame some mid-race interference to finish runner-up over 1800m at the Kensington track last start. Has hardly put a foot wrong this prep and the extra trip looks to come at the right time. The testing material. WIZARD'S STAR (10) is still a maiden but turned in a flashing light run at Canterbury last time out, charging home from last on the corner to be beaten under a length at the end of 1900m. Drops 2.5kgs and is going to be hard to hold out over an extra furlong this time. CALZINO (4) worked home well without threatening in a similar race to this here ten days ago. Rock hard fit and maps nicely. Right in contention. GOLDEN SMILE (5) led and just failed to hold on here at this trip recently. Honest mare who will need to work across from a wide draw but with even luck she should be in the finish. POWERFUL PRAYER (7) is fitter for two runs back from a spell and should go in trifectas and first fours.
